Every year, as the mango season approached, the entire village would buzz with excitement. Children would run through the orchards, playing games and picking up fallen mangoes, while the adults prepared for the harvest. The village elders, with their weathered hands and wise eyes, would share stories of past harvests and the legendary mangoes that once grew in the orchards.
